337
00:31:06,049 --> 00:31:07,360
Please sign it.

338
00:31:27,261 --> 00:31:29,215
I’ll send your request to the headquarter to consider.

339
00:31:30,095 --> 00:31:35,401
If it goes through, I'll have to call the owner of the title deed over.

340
00:31:37,598 --> 00:31:38,321
Okay.

341
00:31:38,596 --> 00:31:39,598
That's not a problem for you, right?

342
00:31:40,350 --> 00:31:41,201
Not at all.

343
00:31:43,910 --> 00:31:45,357
I can use the contact number that's written here, right?

344
00:31:46,451 --> 00:31:47,372
Yes.

345
00:31:55,607 --> 00:31:56,432
Hold on.

346
00:32:00,059 --> 00:32:01,050
That’s my pen.

347
00:32:04,319 --> 00:32:05,358
Sorry.

348
00:32:05,611 --> 00:32:06,847
I'm not aware that I'm taking it.

349
00:32:09,532 --> 00:32:10,398
That’s all right.

350
00:32:11,532 --> 00:32:13,125
Now that you are aware,

351
00:32:14,243 --> 00:32:15,830
just return what you took to me.

352
00:32:53,820 --> 00:32:55,700
[No Answer]

353
00:33:02,586 --> 00:33:03,389
Hey.

354
00:33:03,958 --> 00:33:05,426
How come you are home early?

355
00:33:07,469 --> 00:33:09,225
Stop picking on me.

356
00:33:10,517 --> 00:33:11,894
I’m just asking.

357
00:33:13,022 --> 00:33:13,893
Why?

358
00:33:14,543 --> 00:33:16,620
I'm that much of a jerk to you?

359
00:33:22,652 --> 00:33:25,355
Are you sure you are not picking a fight?

360
00:33:25,763 --> 00:33:27,573
Okay. Let’s be civil.

361
00:33:31,970 --> 00:33:32,820
Alan.

362
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:33,699
Yes?

363
00:33:33,699 --> 00:33:34,798
Can I ask something?

364
00:33:38,237 --> 00:33:42,430
To get a bank loan, can we use someone else’s title deed?

365
00:33:45,568 --> 00:33:48,380
Of course, as long as the owner lets you.

366
00:33:53,358 --> 00:33:54,436
Why?

367
00:33:55,032 --> 00:33:56,441
That man told you to ask me?

368
00:33:58,622 --> 00:34:00,622
He came to my bank today to request a loan.

369
00:34:01,179 --> 00:34:04,424
There are so many banks to choose from, but he chose mine.

370
00:34:08,365 --> 00:34:10,906
Do you think he'll be able to get a loan?

371
00:34:13,845 --> 00:34:15,304
Do you think I’ll approve it?

372
00:34:18,692 --> 00:34:20,450
Is this what you call being civil?

373
00:34:20,450 --> 00:34:21,661
What's wrong with my words?

374
00:34:24,166 --> 00:34:29,306
I’m professional enough to separate work from private matters.

375
00:34:31,068 --> 00:34:34,476
Even if his loan gets declined, I still like him.

376
00:34:57,771 --> 00:35:01,010
Look, guys. We are told to inspect the site today.

377
00:35:01,010 --> 00:35:02,541
Is anyone free to go with me?

378
00:35:03,615 --> 00:35:04,883
I can go with you.

379
00:35:05,127 --> 00:35:07,781
Hold up. Did we get a green light to go ahead with Phase 3?

380
00:35:08,152 --> 00:35:11,343
The contractors are not able to get to the site by the original timelines.

381
00:35:11,343 --> 00:35:16,282
That’s right. Some homeowners are hesitant to sell their properties.

382
00:35:16,282 --> 00:35:17,709
The negotiations are not yet finished.

383
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:19,261
What a waste of time.

384
00:35:20,562 --> 00:35:23,347
If Marina really wants those properties, they should be able to work it out.

385
00:35:23,731 --> 00:35:25,027
That’s true.

386
00:35:25,748 --> 00:35:29,833
But some of the houses near the Chicken Rice place have yet to accept the deals.

387
00:35:34,404 --> 00:35:37,247
What if we fail to acquire those places?

388
00:35:37,518 --> 00:35:39,057
Shouldn’t we delay the project for the time being?

389
00:35:40,953 --> 00:35:42,953
You can go ahead with the project. Don’t wait.

390
00:35:43,228 --> 00:35:45,661
I’m sure the board can sort this out one way or another.

391
00:35:46,131 --> 00:35:47,535
This is Thailand.

392
00:35:48,148 --> 00:35:49,970
Big fish always eat small fish.

393
00:35:51,783 --> 00:35:52,628
Go for it.

394
00:35:55,227 --> 00:35:57,898
Get yourself ready. We are going to the site.

395
00:36:10,748 --> 00:36:11,761
I forgot to tell you this.

396
00:36:11,978 --> 00:36:15,131
Alan asked me about that picture in your Story.

397
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:16,130
He asked me who he is.

398
00:36:21,286 --> 00:36:22,799
What did you say to him?

399
00:36:23,171 --> 00:36:25,279
I said I didn’t know and told him to ask you himself.

400
00:36:28,285 --> 00:36:30,691
Whatever you choose, make it clear.

401
00:36:31,029 --> 00:36:34,220
I have been so clear. We already broke up.

402
00:36:34,485 --> 00:36:36,106
I have nothing else to say to him.

403
00:36:37,904 --> 00:36:39,319
I still don’t understand.

404
00:36:39,563 --> 00:36:41,447
You broke up, but you're still living together.

405
00:36:42,284 --> 00:36:43,743
Isn’t it strange?

406
00:36:47,523 --> 00:36:49,577
Well, he said we could stay as friends.

407
00:36:51,427 --> 00:36:54,158
I understand that part where you can still be friends.

408
00:36:54,158 --> 00:36:54,890
It’s actually nice.

409
00:36:54,890 --> 00:36:56,647
But think about this.

410
00:36:56,647 --> 00:36:59,486
A friend who once was your lover and had intimate relationship with you

411
00:36:59,486 --> 00:37:03,056
stays under the same roof, in the same room and on the same bed as you.

412
00:37:03,452 --> 00:37:04,954
And for a drinker like you,

413
00:37:06,091 --> 00:37:07,374
I’m sure you can get it on easily.

414
00:37:07,954 --> 00:37:09,170
Get it on, my ass.

415
00:37:09,630 --> 00:37:11,199
I’m trying to find a new place to live.

416
00:37:13,451 --> 00:37:14,910
I don’t want to imagine this.

417
00:37:14,910 --> 00:37:17,638
If I’m your new boyfriend and know about this.

418
00:37:18,657 --> 00:37:20,029
I don’t think I can sleep.

419
00:37:21,653 --> 00:37:22,660
Anyway, see you.

420
00:37:22,850 --> 00:37:23,614
See you.

421
00:38:07,003 --> 00:38:07,943
Thank you.

422
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,264
What’s wrong?

423
00:38:48,191 --> 00:38:50,922
Nothing. I just don’t want to talk to you.

424
00:38:52,573 --> 00:38:55,764
Didn’t you say we should talk face to face?

425
00:38:56,737 --> 00:38:57,996
Here I am.

426
00:39:00,243 --> 00:39:01,607
What do you want to talk about? Go ahead.

427
00:39:04,044 --> 00:39:05,557
What do you want me to do?

428
00:39:06,332 --> 00:39:07,791
You can let me know.

429
00:39:10,488 --> 00:39:12,380
I don’t want anything from you, Wen.

430
00:39:13,722 --> 00:39:16,182
I think I made it clear from Day 1.

431
00:39:19,091 --> 00:39:21,984
And now, it couldn’t be any clearer.

432
00:39:25,164 --> 00:39:26,947
Be logical, please.

433
00:39:27,452 --> 00:39:29,398
Alan and I did break up.

434
00:39:29,686 --> 00:39:31,307
We are now friends.

435
00:39:32,233 --> 00:39:33,719
We just live together.

436
00:39:36,192 --> 00:39:38,625
You can have any kind of relationship with anyone. It’s totally up to you.

437
00:39:38,943 --> 00:39:40,510
Don’t involve me.

438
00:39:41,971 --> 00:39:43,130
I’m not a part of it.

439
00:39:44,375 --> 00:39:45,622
You are.

440
00:39:46,009 --> 00:39:47,819
You do know that I like you.

441
00:39:49,876 --> 00:39:53,446
And I’m sure you like me too.

442
00:40:09,109 --> 00:40:09,988
Wen.

443
00:40:10,908 --> 00:40:13,491
Do you remember my question?

444
00:40:14,915 --> 00:40:17,890
I asked you if it’s going to be complicated.

445
00:40:20,340 --> 00:40:21,430
Then what is this?

446
00:40:22,188 --> 00:40:23,639
I’m a grown up man.

447
00:40:24,490 --> 00:40:26,788
I don't like things that are complicated like this.

448
00:40:31,239 --> 00:40:32,360
You got what I meant?

449
00:40:32,929 --> 00:40:34,972
Jim, one Chicken Rice, please.

450
00:40:41,139 --> 00:40:42,760
Sure. Your usual, right?

451
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:43,352
Yes.

452
00:40:43,352 --> 00:40:44,237
Okay, ma’am.

453
00:41:33,999 --> 00:41:35,782
My love was just for you.

454
00:41:37,402 --> 00:41:38,996
But it's no longer that.

455
00:41:39,422 --> 00:41:40,329
It’s suffocating.

456
00:41:40,464 --> 00:41:42,234
Then move out.

457
00:41:42,234 --> 00:41:43,977
Be decisive.

458
00:41:44,324 --> 00:41:46,920
If you continue to stay with him, you will only give him hope.

459
00:41:47,075 --> 00:41:48,297
It’s never going to be over.

460
00:41:49,542 --> 00:41:55,410
I asked you if it’s going to be complicated.

461
00:41:55,613 --> 00:41:56,556
You dumped me

462
00:41:57,206 --> 00:41:59,130
for this Chicken Rice seller?

463
00:41:59,130 --> 00:42:00,725
Hey!

464
00:42:00,928 --> 00:42:01,970
Stay the f**k out!

465
00:42:01,970 --> 00:42:03,290
Calm down.

466
00:42:03,290 --> 00:42:04,327
Then what is this?

467
00:42:04,641 --> 00:42:05,991
I’m a grown up man.

468
00:42:06,330 --> 00:42:08,330
I don't like things that are complicated like this.

469
00:42:08,410 --> 00:42:10,321
You broke up, but you're still living together.

470
00:42:10,321 --> 00:42:12,130
Whatever you choose, make it clear.

471
00:42:24,478 --> 00:42:25,326
Hello, Alan.

472
00:42:30,822 --> 00:42:32,191
Are you free this evening?

473
00:42:35,205 --> 00:42:36,772
Want to go out to eat?

474
00:43:09,828 --> 00:43:10,761
You know what?

475
00:43:11,828 --> 00:43:14,194
I only started to eat beef when I went out with you.

476
00:43:15,482 --> 00:43:16,430
Yes, I know.

477
00:43:17,838 --> 00:43:19,970
When you had that first bite of beef,

478
00:43:19,970 --> 00:43:21,678
I could tell by the look on your face.

479
00:43:22,189 --> 00:43:23,518
You'd clearly never had beef before.

480
00:43:24,573 --> 00:43:25,970
It was our first date.

481
00:43:26,968 --> 00:43:28,968
You even ordered imported beef.

482
00:43:29,716 --> 00:43:31,370
So I ate that to please you.

483
00:43:41,107 --> 00:43:43,324
Now we have just simple cheap beef together.

484
00:43:45,445 --> 00:43:46,619
You know what?

485
00:43:48,243 --> 00:43:50,287
I don’t really like beef.

486
00:43:55,118 --> 00:43:56,631
Then you don’t have to eat it.

487
00:43:57,785 --> 00:43:59,406
But you like it.

488
00:44:01,242 --> 00:44:02,592
I can eat it too.

489
00:44:06,136 --> 00:44:08,298
But now you like chicken better than beef, right?

490
00:44:13,431 --> 00:44:15,702
You were not this sarcastic back then.

491
00:44:18,127 --> 00:44:20,127
I have always been like this.

492
00:44:21,069 --> 00:44:22,852
You just start to not like it.

493
00:44:29,053 --> 00:44:33,679
I told Gong that we broke up.

494
00:44:41,793 --> 00:44:43,970
You brought me here to tell me this?

495
00:44:46,770 --> 00:44:48,662
What about those past 4 or 5 months?

496
00:44:50,509 --> 00:44:52,130
Why did you make me hope?

497
00:44:54,353 --> 00:44:55,970
I was wrong.

498
00:44:58,898 --> 00:45:02,793
Deep down, I also hope we could make it work again.

499
00:45:08,929 --> 00:45:10,408
Everything you did for me,

500
00:45:11,870 --> 00:45:13,257
I saw it.

501
00:45:14,979 --> 00:45:16,229
I'm sorry…

502
00:45:20,154 --> 00:45:21,987
for being the one who fell out of love with you.

503
00:45:29,589 --> 00:45:31,427
But I can't keep lying to myself any longer.

504
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:41,117
Can I ask?

505
00:45:43,472 --> 00:45:45,264
If there’s no one else,

506
00:45:47,969 --> 00:45:49,617
will we reach this point in the relationship?

507
00:45:52,386 --> 00:45:54,034
I asked myself that too.

508
00:45:57,888 --> 00:45:59,646
Even if there was no one else,

509
00:46:03,545 --> 00:46:05,384
it wouldn't be any better.

510
00:46:15,596 --> 00:46:16,747
I'm thinking...

511
00:46:18,723 --> 00:46:21,711
I should make this clear once and for all.

512
00:46:23,301 --> 00:46:24,161
For what?

513
00:46:25,301 --> 00:46:27,280
So that you would feel less like a jackass?

514
00:46:33,084 --> 00:46:34,071
No, Alan.

515
00:46:39,242 --> 00:46:41,419
So that I could finally let you go.

516
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:09,743
Why would you stay with someone who no longer loves you?

517
00:47:16,684 --> 00:47:19,144
Excuse me. I’ll rekindle the fire for you.

518
00:47:19,415 --> 00:47:20,346
No need to.

519
00:47:21,160 --> 00:47:22,483
We’re done. Thanks.

520
00:47:33,381 --> 00:47:35,381
Let’s stop hurting each other.

521
00:47:48,658 --> 00:47:50,441
Now we are truly friends.

522
00:48:10,564 --> 00:48:11,914
You can go first.

523
00:48:56,696 --> 00:48:57,599
Leng.

524
00:48:58,022 --> 00:48:59,795
Please lend me your motorcycle.

525
00:48:59,795 --> 00:49:01,092
Go ahead. The key is over there.

526
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:03,191
Don’t you have to go to Officer Supoch's house?

527
00:49:03,573 --> 00:49:07,743
I'm finished with that. I'm going to Noch's house to work on an assignment.

528
00:49:10,454 --> 00:49:11,381
I’m leaving.

529
00:49:12,170 --> 00:49:13,553
Hold up, Li.

530
00:49:14,151 --> 00:49:15,926
Fill up the tank for me too, my Li bro.

531
00:49:16,289 --> 00:49:17,641
Okay, bro.

532
00:49:27,202 --> 00:49:28,066
Here.

533
00:49:29,841 --> 00:49:30,977
What is it for?

534
00:49:30,977 --> 00:49:32,442
For your gas.

535
00:49:32,840 --> 00:49:34,840
Li Ming has been using your bike.

536
00:49:35,095 --> 00:49:36,926
I would be an ass if I take that.

537
00:49:37,829 --> 00:49:41,971
Wait. But I’ll keep it to buy my baby’s diapers.

538
00:49:43,611 --> 00:49:46,203
You told me not to turn down money, no matter how small.

539
00:49:48,680 --> 00:49:50,877
Have you taken Praew for an ultrasound?

540
00:49:51,683 --> 00:49:53,232
We won’t need that. It’s a waste of money.

541
00:49:55,062 --> 00:49:57,372
A baby girl or baby boy, we raise them the same.

542
00:49:57,372 --> 00:49:59,090
We let them choose their gender identity when they grow up.

543
00:49:59,090 --> 00:50:01,273
Don’t eat your own words later.

544
00:50:01,656 --> 00:50:04,022
Who cares if people are straight or gay these days?

545
00:50:04,350 --> 00:50:06,491
The ones who could make more money are the winners .

546
00:50:15,636 --> 00:50:17,861
Or simply the ones who are happier.

547
00:50:22,283 --> 00:50:23,260
What about you?

548
00:50:23,373 --> 00:50:25,298
When will you find your own happiness?

549
00:50:25,298 --> 00:50:26,066
Huh?

550
00:51:29,795 --> 00:51:33,852
[I've lived in Pattaya since I was born, but I have never been up here before.]

551
00:51:33,852 --> 00:51:35,875
I will bring you back here more often.

552
00:51:36,103 --> 00:51:38,103
[I will bring you back here more often.]

553
00:51:47,334 --> 00:51:49,559
[I haven’t felt this way in a long time.]

554
00:51:55,090 --> 00:51:56,160
What way?

555
00:51:59,060 --> 00:52:01,060
[What way?]

556
00:52:04,930 --> 00:52:07,944
[Like a normal person.]

557
00:52:16,991 --> 00:52:20,231
To me, you’re normal.

558
00:54:05,983 --> 00:54:07,081
Very good.

559
00:54:20,187 --> 00:54:21,342
Oh shit!

560
00:54:34,313 --> 00:54:35,665
[Saleng]

561
00:54:39,399 --> 00:54:40,609
Hello, Leng.

562
00:54:41,088 --> 00:54:43,823
(Where are you now? Uncle Jim is looking for you.)

563
00:54:44,601 --> 00:54:46,263
At the hospital.

564
00:54:46,263 --> 00:54:47,186
(What?)

565
00:54:48,154 --> 00:54:49,478
The bike skidded.

566
00:54:50,001 --> 00:54:53,072
(Holy shit. Are you okay?)

567
00:54:53,574 --> 00:54:54,777
I’m okay.

568
00:54:57,370 --> 00:54:58,646
But Heart.

569
00:54:59,097 --> 00:54:59,953
(What?)

570
00:55:00,417 --> 00:55:01,966
(You went with Heart?)

571
00:55:02,502 --> 00:55:03,826
(Have you told his mom?)

572
00:55:17,009 --> 00:55:19,460
(Hello, Li Ming. Are you still there?)

573
00:55:19,460 --> 00:55:20,932
(Hello.)

574
00:55:30,356 --> 00:55:31,567
Good evening.

575
00:55:40,180 --> 00:55:41,278
Tell us what happened.

576
00:55:59,962 --> 00:56:02,695
I’m sorry. It was my fault.

577
00:56:03,704 --> 00:56:07,095
I taught Heart to ride a motorcycle and it skidded.

578
00:56:09,718 --> 00:56:13,353
We went to the hospital already. It was not serious.

579
00:56:15,984 --> 00:56:17,646
You taught him to ride a motorcycle?

580
00:56:18,366 --> 00:56:20,056
He’s deaf.

581
00:56:21,625 --> 00:56:22,461
Ma’am.

582
00:56:22,912 --> 00:56:24,837
Deaf people can ride motorcycles.

583
00:56:27,205 --> 00:56:28,923
He asked me to teach him how to ride.

584
00:56:30,581 --> 00:56:32,299
But I never gave permission.

585
00:56:33,119 --> 00:56:36,162
Your previous offense has yet to be cleared, and you have now added to it.

586
00:56:37,030 --> 00:56:38,579
Please accept my apologies on behalf of my nephew.

587
00:56:39,267 --> 00:56:41,267
You Li Ming, why did you do it?

588
00:56:41,267 --> 00:56:42,404
Heart asked me to.

589
00:56:42,404 --> 00:56:43,110
Stop saying that.

590
00:56:43,110 --> 00:56:43,825
He was bored staying at home.

591
00:56:43,825 --> 00:56:44,578
I said stop!

592
00:56:47,570 --> 00:56:48,544
There you go again.

593
00:56:49,136 --> 00:56:51,735
You know that he’s mute, so you can say whatever you want?

594
00:56:52,107 --> 00:56:53,459
Mute?

595
00:56:54,827 --> 00:56:58,375
Aren't you aware that deaf people dislike being called mute?

596
00:57:00,985 --> 00:57:02,337
He’s just deaf.

597
00:57:02,337 --> 00:57:03,345
Li Ming.

598
00:57:04,106 --> 00:57:05,571
I said stop.

599
00:57:07,469 --> 00:57:08,511
It’s the truth.

600
00:57:08,511 --> 00:57:09,515
I said stop.

601
00:57:53,850 --> 00:57:55,737
He said you know nothing.

602
00:58:06,326 --> 00:58:08,326
He wants to live his life like everyone else,

603
00:58:09,334 --> 00:58:10,855
not cooped up in here like this.

604
00:58:17,183 --> 00:58:18,192
I…

605
00:58:20,193 --> 00:58:21,184
I…

606
00:58:22,347 --> 00:58:23,417
I…

607
00:58:26,907 --> 00:58:28,415
I don’t know how to…

608
00:58:34,793 --> 00:58:36,793
What did he say?

609
00:58:37,745 --> 00:58:39,520
He's been deaf for 3 years now.

610
00:58:48,143 --> 00:58:50,143
You’ve never tried to learn sign language.

611
00:59:01,364 --> 00:59:02,412
What did he say?

612
00:59:06,775 --> 00:59:07,952
What did he say?

613
00:59:17,502 --> 00:59:22,123
He said that you are ashamed of him being deaf.

614
00:59:29,264 --> 00:59:31,264
I…

615
00:59:32,217 --> 00:59:33,710
Heart, I’m sorry.

616
00:59:34,571 --> 00:59:36,656
I don't know what to say, dear.

617
00:59:37,307 --> 00:59:38,884
Please help tell this to him.

618
00:59:39,059 --> 00:59:40,151
Heart.

619
00:59:40,151 --> 00:59:41,059
Heart!

620
00:59:44,830 --> 00:59:46,024
He’ll be fine, honey.

621
00:59:46,830 --> 00:59:47,861
Just let him for now.

622
01:01:42,952 --> 01:01:44,695
Why do you keep causing trouble after trouble?

623
01:01:46,096 --> 01:01:47,786
It’s not like I want it to happen.

624
01:01:47,943 --> 01:01:49,335
It’s an accident.

625
01:01:49,649 --> 01:01:52,775
It would not have happened if you hadn’t taken him out.

626
01:01:53,806 --> 01:01:55,186
He asked me to.

627
01:01:55,963 --> 01:01:57,766
I’m the only friend he has.

628
01:01:57,896 --> 01:02:00,178
You shouldn’t have taken him out like that.

629
01:02:00,178 --> 01:02:01,777
Be considerate to his parents

630
01:02:01,777 --> 01:02:03,445
What if something more serious occurs to him?

631
01:02:03,445 --> 01:02:04,990
I never think it will occur.

632
01:02:09,897 --> 01:02:11,897
I didn’t say you couldn’t be friends.

633
01:02:12,002 --> 01:02:13,692
But there must be some boundaries.

634
01:02:16,260 --> 01:02:19,951
If I’d become like Heart, you would do the same as Mrs. Jintana does, right?

635
01:02:23,681 --> 01:02:24,834
It’s not the same.

636
01:02:25,681 --> 01:02:30,248
If you have a friend who hasn't left his house in 3 years,

637
01:02:31,550 --> 01:02:34,255
and you are the only person who can take him out,

638
01:02:36,122 --> 01:02:37,558
will you do the same as what I do?

639
01:02:38,955 --> 01:02:40,307
I’m grown enough.

640
01:02:40,757 --> 01:02:42,757
If something happens, I can take responsibility for it.

641
01:02:43,262 --> 01:02:47,009
If I get into trouble again, you don't have to help me.

642
01:02:48,185 --> 01:02:49,565
I'll sort out my own problem.

643
01:03:05,864 --> 01:03:07,103
[Wen]

644
01:03:49,277 --> 01:03:50,967
I don't have a place to stay anymore.

